{"body": "@steveklabnik I think the point is that suddenly relying on the behaviour of a method named `locked` to all relations may not be so great, especially since there's no documented list of scope and class method names to avoid. It's going to cause a bunch of weird interactions, because if you redefine `locked` the query_cache logic is still going to call your redefined method -- and sometimes it'll even still seem to work, but mostly it won't.", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/7732700", "created_at": "2012-08-14T17:09:27Z", "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/6985#issuecomment-7732700", "updated_at": "2012-08-14T17:09:27Z", "repo": "rails", "issue_id": 6985, "user": {"following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/nragaz/following{/other_user}", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/nragaz/events{/privacy}", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/nragaz/orgs", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/nragaz", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/nragaz/gists{/gist_id}", "html_url": "https://github.com/nragaz", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/nragaz/subscriptions", "avatar_url": "https://0.gravatar.com/avatar/18903c149f08850e897d1f63f254eeee?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2F2754518221cfbc8d25c13a06a4cb8421.png", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/nragaz/repos", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/nragaz/received_events", "gravatar_id": "18903c149f08850e897d1f63f254eeee", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/nragaz/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "login": "nragaz", "type": "User", "id": 10078, "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/nragaz/followers"}, "owner": "rails", "_id": {"$oid": "52380133bd3543c15100c0e6"}, "id": 7732700, "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/6985"}
